04749nam a22005055i 9780773566545DE-B159720240306124542.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240306t19981998xxc    fo  d z      eng d  a97807735665457 a10.1515/97807735665452doi  a(DE-B1597)654773  a(OCoLC)732600856  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  axxccCA 4aDA47.9.T8bM54 1998eb 7aHIS0271002bisacsh04a327.4105611 aMillman, Brock, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aIll-Made Alliance :bAnglo-Turkish Relations, 1934-1940 /cBrock Millman. 1aMontreal ;aKingston ;aLondon ;aChicago : bMcGill-Queen's University Press, c[1998] 4c©1998  a1 online resource (536 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFront Matter -- tContents -- tAbbreviations -- tIntroduction -- tParadiso -- tInheritance and Context -- tAtatürk's Gambit, 1934 -- tThe Abyssinian Crisis, 1935 -- tMontreaux, 1936 -- tThe Search for Accommodation, 1936-38 -- tPurgatorio -- tThe Politics of Dependency -- tThe Doldrums, 1938-39 -- tParadox Postponed: The Joint Guarantee, May 1939 -- tThe Military Convention, October 1939 -- tThe Tripartite Treaty, October 1939 -- tInferno -- tPoint d'Armes, Point de Turques, 1939-40 -- tPoint d'Argent, Point d'Armes -- tThe Problem with Germany: The Search for a Strategy, 1939-40 -- tDilemmas in Operational Planning -- tSalvaging the Treaty, 1939-40 -- tThe Debacle, 1940 -- tConclusion -- tAppendices -- tTurkish Weapons Demands: Dec 1937-Jan 1940 -- tTurkish Armaments: Nonallied Orders -- tTurkish Weapons Demands: Deliveries -- tTurkish Weapons Demands: Requested/Pledged/Delivered by June 1940 -- tAdjusted Turkish Requirements of Raw Materials -- tTraining Assistance Desired (Outside Turkey) -- tNotes -- tBibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn 1939, faced with the German invasion of Czechoslovakia and a growing Italian threat in the Balkans, Turkey and Britain (and later France) signed an alliance in which Turkey linked itself politically and militarily with Britain and France in exchange for financial assistance for its rearmament program. Despite the agreement, however, when the war came to the Mediterranean, Turkey did not become involved. Presenting a new interpretation of why the alliance failed, Brock Millman explores Anglo-Turkish relations leading up to the alliance of 1939, taking into account the broader economic, military, and strategic issues.While previous accounts suggest that Turkey entered into the alliance reluctantly, Millman contends that it not only wanted an alliance but sought as close a relationship as Britain would concede in the prewar years. He attributes the failure of the alliance mainly to Britain's lack of support, namely its inability to fit Turkey into its strategy in the Mediterranean, its failure to produce a coherent operational plan that could encompass Turkish military co-operation, and its unwillingness to provide Turkey with timely and much-needed financial, material, and industrial assistance.Divided into three parts, The Ill-Made Alliance examines the roots and course of the Anglo-Turkish rapprochement in the years 1934-38; the economic, military, and politic factors in 1938-39 that inhibited development of the emerging alliance to the point where it might have been fully functional; and the collapse of the alliance in 1939-40.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aHISTORY / Military / World War II.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780773566545?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773566545423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773566545/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  aGBV-deGruyter-alles